name: Lowe's
directions: Along the front wall in front of the self check outs.

name: Target
directions: The restroom by the cvs
comment: Target is pretty chill, you can use what ever bathroom in the front that you want to and workers shouldn't give you a hard time. If you feel more safe in a one stall restroom, they have one by the pharmacy.

name: University of Manchester Students' Union
directions: On the ground floor, to the right of the reception desk when you walk in the front door

name: Dave's Coffee
directions: Bathroom door behind front door when you come in

name: Savoy Bookshop and Cafe
directions: Bottom floor, around the staircase

name: Dizzy's Diner
directions: The red door in the back
comment: Usually the staff will let you use it even if you're not buying anything but it deprnds who's working. It gets very busy during brunch (weekend mornings).

name: The Plate
directions: Past the counters and cart into the little hallway
comment: People walk in just to use the bathroom all the time, we don't enforce anything.

name: Southland Books
directions: In cafe

name: VCA Cedar Animal Hospital
directions: In waiting room
comment: Bathroom is by front desk, you will be welcomed.

name: George's Fish Bar
directions: At the back, past the dining area

name: Memorial Medical Center
directions: Medical Arts Building, second floor. There's one on each patient floor as well.
comment: Visitor. Just come in.

name: Virtua Fitness Center
directions: Walk in through the main entrance and turn left, past the hair salon on your right, and just before you hit the front desk for the gym there's a little hallway on your right. The bathrooms are in that hallway. Just ask the gym front desk if you're not sure.
comment: You can't really go past the gym desk if you're not a member, but the bathrooms are before the desk so anyone's good to use them. If you are looking for a gym, this one's on the pricier side but they do have a co-ed locker room with single stall lockable showers. They also offer a "free first day" you can discreetly use if you're in need of a place to shower, though you'll want to act like you're looking to use the gym itself.

name: Habitat Tavern and Commons
directions: Near the gendered bathrooms. Clearly marked.

name: Half Price Books
directions: In the back by the clearance shelves.

name: Old Spruce Restaurant
comment: Need to be a paying customer

name: KPA Clubhouse
directions: Where the other toilets are
comment:
Nice, large space (doubles as disabled).
Don't have to be a paying customer.

name: Pin Oak Park
directions: It's in the middle of the park near some basketball courts and a large shelter.
comment: They're dirty, being so public, but bearable. They're on the opposite side of the shelter area so they're kinda private but they do face the basketball courts. They are each single person rooms with deadbolt locks on the doors and, seem to be open 24 hours. I went on a walk and used one of them around 1 in the morning. The area was very well lit, as well.

name: TRADE
directions: Ground floor underneath Black Whiskey. All the way in the back of the bar, one unisex bathroom.
comment: It's a gay bar that has supportive and open-minded management and employees. Clientele is on the friendlier side for a gay bar, too, but there are still some cis/white assholes every once in a while.

name: Pease Public Library
directions: Walk right in the front doors past the circulation desk. It is on your left right before the room with the huge window.

name: Pomegranate Cafe
directions: it's in the back, near the kitchen. there's a sign on the door of a little restroom man with a pomegranate for a head :)
comment: the workers are super friendly and very understanding, but depending on who's working you may have to buy something. they have baked goods for sale and also sell veggies and stuff, along with their whole cafe thing.

name: Marks of Art Tattoo
comment: Customers only

name: Wonder Waffel Wedding
directions: At the back on the left, next to the stairs.
comment: For customers, but easy to act like one. Very narrow. Not explicitly trans friendly, but there is just a single stall and a little room with a sink.

name: Coffee Society
directions: To the right of the counter
comment: Look like you're gonna buy something (or not it doesn't really matter)

name: Smirtorget
directions: right next to the pharmacy
comment: there's two: one that's accessible and one that's not

name: Gunn High School
directions: by the villages, or near the bus stop
comment: ask the main office for directions if you can't find it, they are very supportive :)

name: Starbucks
comment: You'll just have to ask for the access code.

name: Starbucks
comment: You just need a code to get into the bathroom

name: Barrington Coffee Roasters
comment: It's a small place, so it's clear to the baristas if you're just using the restroom.

name: St Cross College
directions: Located between the Common Room and the Hall.

name: Starbucks
directions: There are two restrooms in the back, passed the counter. For handicap accessibility, one should enter through the door from Main St.

name: Bodrum Kitchen
directions: Small door by the exit
comment: Paying customer

name: deco titirangi
directions: Back of the restaurant behind kitchen
comment: Paying customer

name: Bluebells Tearoom
directions: Toilet is through the back
comment: You should buy something, but if it's an emergency and you ask nicely they'll probably let you through - they are good people.

name: Fred Meyer
directions: At the front of the store by customer service desk. Between the men's and women's rooms.
comment: Single room, has a changing table for babies.

name: Pakhuis de Zwijger
directions: Follow the signs.
comment: Gendered bathrooms, but it's a progressive place. They're unlikely to care.

name: Rugby College
directions: Through main entrance, go up to first floor. It's opposite the elevator
comment: Students only

name: ArtEZ
directions: The bathroom is in the hall when you come in. Beneath the stairs.
comment: It's an art school. Despite the gendered bathrooms people will not care where you go to pee. No need to be a student either, it's a big place, just come in. They are closed in the summer though.

name: Sons of Haiti Food Cart Pod
directions: Behind the M W St Joseph Grand Lodge, at the intersection of Fremont St and the alley between Michigan Ave and Mississippi Ave.
comment: This is a permanent port-a-potty serving the Sons of Haiti Food Cart Pod. Enter from Fremont if you don't want to be seen.

name: Grizzl
directions: It's a small hipstery burger place with one stall. Behind the wooden boards on the left side.
comment: I haven't tried using the restroom without being a paying customer, but at least it's one single stall wil no gender sign.

name: Park Place Mall
directions: Family restrooms are located near the southeast corner of the food court and a corridor near the main halls crossing.

name: Rite Aid
directions: Straight back to the pharmacy. Ask for key at pharmacy

name: Battle Ground Community Library
directions: Family/single stall restroom in the same hallway as the gendered restrooms.
comment: The Libary's policy is that patrons and vistors may use whichever bathroom they are most comfortable in, and that anyone who is uncomfortable can use the family/single stall restroom.

name: Chipotle
directions: In the back of the store

name: Subway
directions: Located in the southeast corner of the restaurant, left of the service counter.

name: Thaitations
directions: Two single-occupancy restrooms are in the northwest corner of the restaurant.

name: Tacoma community College
directions: In building 13, take a right after entering front door.

name: Trader Joe's
directions: To the right, in the back by the sample counter

name: Cobb Theaters- Tyrone Luxury 10
directions: In front of the people who accept your tickets, across from the food.

name: Starbucks
directions: On the right hand side after you enter there are two, roomy, unisex, individual bathrooms.

name: Heriot-Watt University
directions: Postgraduate Centre (first building with blue corner front and glass) ground floor and second floor gender neutral accessible single stall.
comment: Building open to all on campus until about 7pm.

name: Foxy Loxy Cafe
directions: Through the front entrance, to the left, towards the back in the hall that leads out the rear of the building. Clearly labeled.

name: The Graham
directions: All bathrooms are gender neutral and single stall

name: Foxy Loxy Cafe
directions: Through the front entrance, to the left, towards the back in the hall that leads out the rear of the building. Clearly labeled.
comment: Gendered, but are single person use.

name: Foxy Loxy Cafe
directions: Through the front entrance, to the left, towards the back in the hall that leads out the rear of the building. Clearly labeled.
comment: Gendered, but are single person use.

name: Caffé Rococo
directions: In the back to your left.
comment: Please be kind to these people. Everyone I've met here is amazingly friendly and pleasant. Restrooms are open to the public thus far. No key or code required.

name: Sushi Zen
directions: Its a very small establishment, but the bathrooms are in the back and easy to spot.
comment: Gendered, but single person bathrooms.

name: Boe Chapel Undercroft
directions: Go downstairs, there are a few gender neutral stalls that line the hallway

name: Seasons of Change Behavioral Health
directions: Building a daycare, walk down the hallway all the way down
comment: Single stall

name: FuManChu Cupcakes
directions: To the right as you walk in
comment: There are two labeled unisex/gender neutral single stalls available for use. They aren't labeled for customers only, but this place sells awesome local art and amazing cupcakes, so take a look around and support them if you can.

name: Stater Bros. Markets
directions: Located behind double doors in the center of the very back wall. Through the double doors, there are two single-stall gendered bathrooms to the immediate left.
comment: You should be able to just walk in.

name: San Diego Miramar College Library
directions: In the library which is on the second floor. The bathroom is on the right from entrance door. Says "Unisex" on it.

name: Gman Tavern
directions: The two bathrooms in the front bar are single use and not gendered. The two in the back are larger and are gendered.
comment: Punk bar. Everyone is welcome here.

name: Anh and Chi
directions: To the right of the front door against the back wall.

name: Starbucks
comment: They should just let you go in and use it I don't think this location has ever required a key or passcode to get into the bathrooms.

name: The Steeping Room
directions: Directly on the left after you enter. There are two closed-door restrooms that are each labeled gender neutral.

name: SO36
directions: Doors for both gendered toilets have "Trans" listed

name: Bass Pro Shops
directions: Walk through the main entrance, take a right, walk past the main restrooms, there are two "family" bathrooms

name: Taper Hall, USC
directions: Second floor, south end of building in Slavic/Classics wing
comment: A little tricky to find—to the east of the main hallway

name: Bar Bandini
directions: Walk to the back of the bar and turn down the only hallway to the left.
comment: You have to walk past the bar itself to get to it.

name: Bar Bandini
directions: In the back, hallway to the left

name: Bar Bandini
directions: In the back, hallway to the left

name: Drs. Roy and Associates Eye Care
directions: Down the hall and slightly to the left

name: Chupacabra Cantina
directions: Just at the top of the stairs' landing inside. Next to the gendered restrooms there is a handicapped, single-stall, gender neutral restroom.
comment: You can probably use this restroom if you just go in and pretend you know someone eating inside or at the bar.

name: McDonald's
directions: Single unisex stall just inside the store.
comment: Open 24 hours. You can generally go in and use the restroom without having to buy anything (nobody has ever said anything to me).

name: At the Wallace
directions: Three single occupancy stalls at the back of the bar.
comment: Usually open 3 PM-4 AM. Must be 21+ to enter.

name: Black Crown Coffee
directions: First floor between stairs and back counter.
comment: Have to be paying customer and ask barista for key. Staff is friendly and welcoming to all.

name: Winco foods grocery
directions: Through the front door, to the left, pass customer service, almost at the end of the wall
comment: No problems with going in just to pee!
